rComments: Fall 2012. What an approachable, passionate, and interesting prof. She is one of the best that I have had in the last two years. She knows her subject very well and strongly encourages class engagement. She'll hear your opinion and build on it while offering other opinions that she has been exposed to in her research. Simply divine professor.

Prof. Rubright's enthusiasm is infectious. She forces you to think about material in new ways, and challenges you to think beyond the surface. She expects a LOT, which can get seriously overwhelming, but she's approachable and flexible if you show that you are willing to put effort into her class. One of the best English profs I had @ UTSC!

Don't be afraid of the giant Shakespeare anthology you have to lug around, really that's the worst part. The class is fun and interesting and she does a great job teaching it. Not too many assignments, mid term and exam are worth 80% overall.

Professor Rubright may seem extremely provocative at first but if you do your work and take one step in attempting to do good, she will help you along the way. All her rules and planning scared me at first but when you talk to her, she is EXTREMELY nice and will go out of her way to help you by making the midterm easier and extra credit performance

a very fair prof. She is very detailed, and requires student to keep up with the readings, but in the end it is all worth it. She is VERY lenient and willing to help student at all cost even if it means re-arranging the syllabus when the class agreed the work load was weighty. Exams r VERY FAIR. GOOD PROF
